.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-OBSERVE 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.9.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-observe \- read live and staged Grafana state through a shared observe surface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util observe [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
read live and staged Grafana state through one canonical observe surface.
.PP
when you want readiness, overview, snapshot, or direct live reads without moving into mutation work.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B live
render a live readiness view from Grafana read surfaces. Use when: Need the current estate state and want to gate follow\-on work.
.TP
.B staged
render a readiness gate from staged artifacts. Use when: Want to inspect exported files, desired state, or bundle inputs before apply.
.TP
.B overview
summarize staged artifacts or open the live overview. Use when: Want one estate\-wide summary across dashboards, alerts, datasources, access, or bundle inputs.
.TP
.B snapshot
review or export a snapshot\-style artifact bundle. Use when: Want a portable artifact package for inspection, review, or handoff.
.TP
.B resource
inspect one live Grafana resource directly. Use when: Already know the resource kind and want get, list, describe, or kinds style reads.
